public interface CastableMap<K,V> extends Map<K,V>
Specialization of a Map that allows casting stored values. Several default methods are provided to easily cast to common types.
Since:
1.0.0
Author:
Khyonie

    • of

      @NotNull static <K> CastableMap<K,Object> of(Object... pairs) throws IllegalArgumentException, ClassCastException
      Creates a new modifiable, castable map with the specified mappings. If no mappings are provided, an empty map is returned.
      Type Parameters:
      K - Key type. All odd elements in the array MUST be of this type (I.E Element 0 must be of the same type as element 2, 4, and so on)
      Parameters:
      pairs - Mappings with which to construct a map
      Returns:
      A modifiable, castable map with the specified mappings.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - If the array of pairs contains an odd number of elements
      ClassCastException - If one or more key object classes does not match the class of the first key object.
      Since:
      1.0.0
